=============================================================================
			SMACQ BUILD INSTRUCTIONS

Debian GNU/Linux:
-----------------
1. Run the following command to install the Debian packages require to compile
and execute this package:
	apt-get install \
		zlib1g zlib1g-dev \
		libglib2.0 libglib2.0-dev \
		libpcap0 libpcap-dev \
		libtool docbook-to-man groff python2.2-dev wget

2. Run "make" to build

MacOS/X - Fink:
----------------
1. Run the following command to install the Fink packages require to compile
and execute this package:
	apt-get install \
		dlcompat zlib glib2-dev libpcap libpcap-shlibs \
		libtool docbook-bundle groff python wget 

2. Run "gnumake" to build

Other Operating Systems:
------------------------
The SMACQ build procedure depends on GNU Make and the GNU loader.
By installing the equivalent of the packages listed for the above
operating systems, and passing the correct arguments to Make, you
should be able to build SMACQ.  Contributions of documentation for 
building on other operating systems would be appreciated.

=============================================================================
		   	    MISCELLANEOUS NOTES
	
The libsmacq/sql build depends on:
	bison flex

=============================================================================
See http://smacq.sourceforge.net/ for more information.




